5000|$|The Sentinel boiler was {{designed}} to cope with these problems, and to permit easy cleaning of the waterspace. As well as the usual <b>blow-down</b> <b>cock</b> for daily use, the entire boiler could be dismantled easily. The outer shell was in two sections, inner and outer drum, and were joined by a bolted ring joint at top and bottom. Regular servicing (depending on water conditions) was to separate the water-tubes in their drum from the boiler outer shell, {{so that they could}} be cleaned. Sludge dropped free on opening the shell and the short, straight tubes could easily be cleaned with brush or scraper.|$|E

